---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [{ label: 'Editorial Policy', href: '/editorial-policy/' }];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Policy — MyHormoneGuide"
  description="How MyHormoneGuide selects, writes, reviews, and updates content. Our commitment to accuracy, independence, and E-E-A-T standards."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-14">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-navy-600 mb-4">Editorial Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-10">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>How We Select Topics</h2>
      <p>
        Topics are selected based on patient search behavior, gaps in available patient-facing information, and clinical relevance to our audience. We prioritize questions that real patients are asking that aren't being answered clearly by existing resources.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not accept payment to write about specific topics. Sponsored content is always clearly labeled.
      </p>

      <h2>How Content Is Written</h2>
      <p>
        All content is written with the following standards:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Primary sources are preferred: published studies, clinical guidelines, and statements from recognized medical organizations (Endocrine Society, NAMS, etc.).</li>
        <li>Claims are attributed to their source. We distinguish between established consensus, emerging research, and contested areas.</li>
        <li>Language is patient-appropriate: clear, warm, and free of unnecessary jargon.</li>
        <li>Medical recommendations are avoided. We educate; we do not prescribe.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Medical Review Process</h2>
      <p>
        Articles that make specific clinical claims are reviewed by a healthcare practitioner with relevant expertise before publication. Reviewer credentials are disclosed on the article.
      </p>

      <h2>Updates and Corrections</h2>
      <p>
        Medical information changes. We review content regularly and update articles when new research or clinical guidelines warrant it. Update dates are reflected in article metadata.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you identify an error or outdated information, please email us at <strong>hello@myhormoneguide.com</strong>. We take accuracy seriously and respond to correction requests promptly.
      </p>

      <h2>Independence</h2>
      <p>
        Our editorial team operates independently of our advertising and partnership functions. Advertisers, sponsors, and affiliate partners have no influence over editorial decisions, topic selection, or content.
      </p>

      <h2>AI-Assisted Content</h2>
      <p>
        Some content on MyHormoneGuide is produced with AI writing assistance. All AI-assisted content is reviewed, edited, and fact-checked by a human editor before publication. We use AI as a drafting tool, not as a replacement for editorial judgment or medical review.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
